Shesha is great and RLMs can give you excellent long-context reasoning over massive sets of documents (I'll be releasing a "Document Explorer" soon. Just upload tons of docs and query them). But I wanted something that wouldn't take me too much out of my workflow. So with the release of Claude Opus 4.6, I created a Claude Skill that is special-purposed for this task. (It's a massive prompt). Opus's coherence and its ability to dispatch and manage tons of subagents has taken this architecture prompt and made it a great tool.

